Uttar Pradesh is a state in northern India; with over 200 million residents, it is the most populous state in the India (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uttar_Pradesh). Uttar Pradesh has a humid subtropical climate with 4 seasons: the winter in January and February is followed by summer (pre-monsoon) between March and May, the monsoon season between June and September, and the post-monsoon (northeast monsoon) between October and December. Lucknow, with a population of 2.8 million residents in 2011, is the capital and largest city in Uttar Pradesh (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lucknow). - Mod.ML

Reliable and timely laboratory support in hospitals and private clinics attending these encephalitis cases is critical in order to obtain a reliable diagnosis. Although scrub typhus may be responsible for many cases categorized as acute encephalitis syndrome (AES), other etiological agents have been implicated in the past. The determination of the etiology or etiologies of AES has been confusing and elusive. AES has been attributed to a variety of etiologies, including Reye syndrome-like disease, possible enterovirus infection from polluted water, heat stroke, scrub typhus (_Orientia tsutsugamushi_), and lychee fruit consumption. Japanese encephalitis virus infections have been shown to be responsible for some of these cases. Prospective studies should help to rule out or include these etiologies. - Mod.TY

